President Obama has nominated Goodwin Liu for the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit and Judge Robert N. Chatigny for the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit. Goodwin Liu is an Associate Dean and Professor of Law at the University of California, Berkeley School of Law, and is an expert in constitutional law and education law and policy. Judge Chatigny has been serving as a U.S. District Judge for the District of Connecticut since 1994 and was Chief Judge from 2003 to 2009. Both nominees have been recognized for their legal expertise and public service.